WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:24.000
NiyamGuard is a synthetic policy-compliance and citizen-service sandbox, not an official government portal.

00:24.000 --> 00:52.000
GO-138 changes Income Certificate validity from 12 months to 6 months. Ingestion, extraction, human review, publication, and propagation remain separate states.

00:52.000 --> 01:35.000
The real end-to-end simulation creates reviewed policy state, checks mock systems, creates a synthetic application and simulated payment, performs officer review, issues a demo certificate, verifies it, and records audit evidence.

01:35.000 --> 02:03.000
The hybrid engine answers from the verified source. Optional Ollama explanation falls back honestly when the local model is unavailable.

02:03.000 --> 02:50.000
Mock systems are reset to the stale 12-month value, then the explicit demo workflow publishes and patches them to the verified 6-month rule. No real portal is contacted.

02:50.000 --> 03:28.000
The citizen portal answers a validity question from the same verified rule and shows provenance. It does not auto-fill or submit an official application.

03:28.000 --> 03:52.000
The generated demo certificate is verified using the simulation hash. This is not a government signature or certificate authority.

03:52.000 --> 04:10.000
The operations dashboard derives compliance and coverage scores from assessed findings and checked connected systems.

04:10.000 --> 04:30.000
Policy lineage links immutable versions to source, prior version, knowledge refresh, propagation work, compliance runs, and rollback evidence.

04:30.000 --> 04:48.000
The searchable knowledge-relationship view traces verified rules into connected systems and visible drift status.

04:48.000 --> 05:08.000
Audit evidence makes sandbox actions reviewable. Tests, builds, dependency checks, and secret scans support a strong local prototype claim.

05:08.000 --> 05:28.000
Real deployment still requires authorized integrations, managed secrets, privacy, accessibility, security, legal, and department review.
